    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-04-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-04-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="503" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d503">
                <head>No. 499.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Señor <persName type="to">de
                                    Zamacona</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-04-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 28,
                                1881</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my note of the 19th instant
                            in reply to yours of the 13th relative to the depredations upon citizens
                            of Mexico by outlaws, presumed to have their lurking place in Arizona
                            Territory, I have now the honor and the pleasure to inform you that the
                            Secretary of the Interior advises me that he has requested, by his
                            letter of the 21st instant, the governor of that Territory to exert all
                            means within his power to suppress such disturbances and to maintain
                            quiet on the frontier.</p>
                <p>Accept, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JAMES G. BLAINE.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
